# Athlete Goals

This document describes the athlete's goals across performance, training, health, and long-term development.
Agents should use these goals to guide recommendations, maintain alignment across disciplines, and ensure training decisions support long-term progress.

---

## 1. Primary Performance Goals

### A. [Target Race Distance] Performance
- Achieve a **[goal time]** at [race name or distance].
- Execute an evenly paced race supported by strong fueling and hydration.
- Arrive at race day feeling fresh, not overtrained.

### B. Secondary Distance Performance
- Continue improving [secondary distance] times, targeting **[sub-X:XX]** as a medium-term milestone.

---

## 2. Short-Term Training Goals (Current Training Phase)

- Maintain consistency with a **[X]-day running schedule**.
- Complete scheduled weekly quality sessions and long runs when recovery allows.
- Improve ability to sustain **[target pace]** efforts for extended durations.
- Continue refining race-day fueling strategy.

---

## 3. Long-Term Development Goals

- Build durable aerobic capacity capable of supporting annual [marathon/half marathon] cycles.
- Improve running economy through consistent aerobic development, strength training, and mobility work.
- Establish a sustainable training foundation compatible with work and family life.

---

## 4. Strength & Mobility Goals

### Strength Goals
- Develop strong, balanced lower-body musculature (glutes, hamstrings, quads, calves).
- Build core stability to support efficient running form.
- Avoid strength sessions that cause excessive DOMS or interfere with key runs.

### Mobility Goals
- Maintain healthy mobility in ankles, calves, hips, hamstrings, and thoracic spine.

---

## 5. Health & Lifestyle Goals

- Support recovery with adequate sleep.
- Maintain healthy body weight and energy balance.
- Prevent excessive fatigue or overreaching.
- Fuel effectively for training and recovery.

---

## 6. Race Execution Goals

- Arrive at key races adequately tapered, healthy, and confident in pacing.
- Execute race strategy with even pacing and appropriate early-race restraint.
- Minimize GI issues, dehydration, and performance drop-off in later miles.

---

This document should be referenced by all agents to ensure training decisions support the athlete's short- and long-term goals.
